I’m unable to reproduce the issue to pinpoint the cause but the memory issue seems serious. The issue needs further investigation.
Note that both the the reports we've seen of this issue happen on windows.

@vlkigdm and anyone else having this problem, you can disable embedded DevTools by going to Preferences -> Languages & Frameworks -> Flutter and unchecking "Enable embedding DevTools ..." under Experiments.

This may have been fixed with https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/pull/5035, which should mean one browser instance is reused. @vlkigdm can you let me know what version of the Flutter IntelliJ plugin you're using?
